  "text": "Husarova et al. note that decisions to refuse blood transfusion, often made when well, can radically change in health-and life-threatening circumstance of obstetric haemorrhage [CITATION_1] . In cases of severe blood loss it is thus suggested to reconfirm the patient's position on acceptance of blood products.",
